Hey all!  My company Intrepid Pursuits (<http://intrepid.io>) is looking for a few Senior (3+ years experience, apps in the store, etc) Android devs to join our rapidly growing team. DM me if you'd like to chat about it!  Also feel free to forward to friends.

> Rates need to be low, they don’t need senior, they need smart folks.

Android – 2 roles
·         Someone who knows the base of android, container, threading, android security, studio kit, java, sdk
·         They are not looking for senior candidates, they need someone with 2 to 4 years, young, someone who is not afraid to solve problems, can work long hours, culture is the key here, the hiring manager kept talking about culture.
Rates need to be low, they don’t need senior, they need smart folks. The client is building a platform that no one has attempted to build, someone who can face challenges, someone who does not want to focus on one skill and be open to learning new skills, think logically, interview will be to write pseudo codes.
